---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Personal Projects - Anton Malienko"
  description="Personal projects and tools developed for SEO automation, data analysis, and web development"
>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Personal Projects</h1>

    <p>I build tools and applications to automate SEO processes, analyze data, and solve real-world problems. Here are some of my personal projects:</p>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>SEO Technical Audit Automation Tool</h2>
      <p><strong>Technologies:</strong> Python, Selenium, BeautifulSoup, Pandas</p>
      <p><strong>Description:</strong> A comprehensive Python-based tool that automates technical SEO audits for large-scale websites. The tool crawls websites, identifies technical issues, and generates detailed reports.</p>
      <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Automated crawling and analysis of website structure</li>
        <li>Detection of common technical SEO issues (broken links, duplicate content, missing meta tags)</li>
        <li>Page speed analysis and recommendations</li>
        <li>Structured data validation</li>
        <li>Automated report generation with prioritized action items</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>NLP Content Optimization Platform</h2>
      <p><strong>Technologies:</strong> Python, spaCy, NLTK, TensorFlow, Flask</p>
      <p><strong>Description:</strong> A natural language processing application that analyzes content for SEO optimization opportunities using machine learning.</p>
      <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Topic modeling and content gap analysis</li>
        <li>Keyword extraction and semantic analysis</li>
        <li>Content readability scoring</li>
        <li>Competitive content analysis</li>
        <li>AI-powered content recommendations</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>Ecommerce Image Labeling with Computer Vision</h2>
      <p><strong>Technologies:</strong> Python, TensorFlow, OpenCV, Keras</p>
      <p><strong>Description:</strong> A computer vision system that automatically generates accurate, SEO-friendly alt text and labels for ecommerce product images.</p>
      <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Custom trained image classification model</li>
        <li>Automated alt text generation for products</li>
        <li>Batch processing of thousands of images</li>
        <li>Quality control and validation mechanisms</li>
        <li>Integration with popular ecommerce platforms</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>Rank Tracking & Analytics Dashboard</h2>
      <p><strong>Technologies:</strong> Python, JavaScript, React, PostgreSQL, Chart.js</p>
      <p><strong>Description:</strong> A custom-built rank tracking and analytics platform for monitoring SEO performance across multiple websites and search engines.</p>
      <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Automated daily rank tracking for thousands of keywords</li>
        <li>Historical data analysis and trending</li>
        <li>Competitor rank monitoring</li>
        <li>Interactive data visualizations</li>
        <li>Customizable alerts and reporting</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>Log File Analyzer for SEO</h2>
      <p><strong>Technologies:</strong> Python, Pandas, Matplotlib, Apache Log Parser</p>
      <p><strong>Description:</strong> A specialized tool for analyzing server log files to understand search engine crawler behavior and optimize crawl budget.</p>
      <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Parse and analyze large log files (millions of requests)</li>
        <li>Identify crawler behavior patterns</li>
        <li>Crawl budget analysis and optimization recommendations</li>
        <li>Detection of crawler errors and issues</li>
        <li>Visualization of crawler activity over time</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>Schema Markup Generator</h2>
      <p><strong>Technologies:</strong> JavaScript, Node.js, JSON-LD</p>
      <p><strong>Description:</strong> A web application that generates structured data markup for various schema types, making it easy to implement rich snippets.</p>
      <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Support for multiple schema types (Product, Article, FAQ, etc.)</li>
        <li>Visual editor for schema creation</li>
        <li>Validation against Google's structured data requirements</li>
        <li>Bulk schema generation for ecommerce catalogs</li>
        <li>Export in JSON-LD format</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Open Source Contributions</h2>
    <p>I also contribute to open-source SEO tools and libraries when possible. If you're interested in collaborating on a project or want to learn more about any of these tools, feel free to <a href="mailto:antonmalienko@gmail.com">reach out</a>!</p>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .project {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
  }

  .project:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .project h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
</style>
